    "recap_headline": "Long Beach State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LONG BEACH, Calif.\n\u2014\nJake Evans\ngave Long Beach State an early spark with a first-inning solo home run, but Hawai'i answered with six runs in the second inning and pulled away for an 11-1 win Friday night in Big West action at Bohl Diamond at Blair Field.\nEvans accounted for the Dirtbags' lone run with his first homer of the season, while\nTrevor Goldenetz\nand\nSmith Chandler\neach collected two hits in the loss. Hawai'i starter Isaiah Magdaleno held Long Beach State to one run over six innings and struck out nine.\nAfter\nJake Fields\nstarted and recorded two strikeouts in the opening inning, the Dirtbags turned to\nJoey Iglesias\n,\nCaleb Anderson\n,\nKa'imi Kahalekai\nand\nMason Tymick\nout of the bullpen. Anderson worked 4.1 innings and struck out five, while Tymick closed the final two innings without allowing a hit and added two strikeouts.\nIn the eighth inning,\nDamon Valdez\ncame off the bench to bat against his brother, Hawai'i reliever Derek Valdez, grounding out in the family matchup.\nLong Beach State will look to bounce back in Game 2 of the series Saturday, with first pitch set for 6:05 p.m. on ESPN+."
